{CRIEFF CARRY-ON WEEK}
This is the name given to the week which marks the start of the tourist season for Crieff. It was the idea of the Crieff Round Table and consists of a week full of competitions and events of interest to the tourist and local alike. It starts on a Sunday with a parade of floats through the town which have been built by the different clubs and societies in Crieff, and these are then judged. This year's winners were the Brownies, whose theme was "MARY MARY QUITE CONTRARY".
A new event this year was a junior version of "It's a knock-out" which was won by the boys' team from Crieff Primary School.
